    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Configuration Management</title>
        <para>This data module describes the configuration management approach for the 
        AQUA-OS operating system, including version control, configuration items, and 
        change control procedures.</para>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Configuration Items</title>
          <para>The following configuration items are under formal control:</para>
          <para>- Kernel source code and build scripts</para>
          <para>- Partition schedule configuration (schedule.xml)</para>
          <para>- Health monitoring tables (HM_Table.xml)</para>
          <para>- Memory allocation maps (memory_map.xml)</para>
          <para>- I/O configuration and device drivers</para>
        </levelledPara>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Version Control</title>
          <para>All configuration items are managed in version control:</para>
          <para>- Git repository with signed commits</para>
          <para>- Branch protection for safety-critical components</para>
          <para>- Automated CI/CD validation</para>
          <para>- Release tagging with UTCS canonical hashes</para>
        </levelledPara>
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Change Control</title>
          <para>Changes follow formal change control process:</para>
          <para>- Change request documentation</para>
          <para>- Safety impact analysis</para>
          <para>- Verification testing</para>
          <para>- Configuration Control Board approval</para>
        </levelledPara>
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
